<p><strong>April 9, 2020 –</strong> The following is a letter that was sent from Superintendent Paul Enderle to the District123 community regarding recent school closure and coronavirus information.</p>
<hr>
<p>School Closure Update for April 9, 2020</p>
<p>Thank you for another great week of Remote Learning at District 123!</p>
<p>Words cannot express my continued pride and gratitude for what we have accomplished so far. I would like to personally thank our entire community for pulling together to care for one another. Additionally, we value each opportunity to work together and ensure that our children have access to high-quality learning opportunities throughout this unprecedented time. We are proud to have:</p>
<ul>
<li>Served 24,948 Grab &amp; Go Meals</li>
<li>Engaged nearly 80% of our students each day</li>
<li>Participated in over 3,220 virtual meetings with students and staff</li>
<li>Received 721 responses to our first Remote eLearning Survey</li>
<li>Collected over 450 cards and art projects for First Responders and Healthcare workers</li>
<li>Served 7,653 unique users on the <a href="http://track.spe.schoolmessenger.com/f/a/3KfBqLttSNkeypwx1dJa6w~~/AAAAAQA~/RgRgcMipP0QaaHR0cHM6Ly9lTGVhcm5pbmcuZDEyMy5vcmdXB3NjaG9vbG1CCgAAKZWPXs9XEXpSEW5zeW1vbmRzQGQxMjMub3JnWAQAAAAB" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://track.spe.schoolmessenger.com/f/a/3KfBqLttSNkeypwx1dJa6w~~/AAAAAQA~/RgRgcMipP0QaaHR0cHM6Ly9lTGVhcm5pbmcuZDEyMy5vcmdXB3NjaG9vbG1CCgAAKZWPXs9XEXpSEW5zeW1vbmRzQGQxMjMub3JnWAQAAAAB&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1586955173166000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEtXByPZKPWTTNxXdLK5FKIsruDFQ">eLearning.d123.org</a> remote learning resource site</li>
<li>Donated 5,440 essential items to First Responders and Health Care Providers</li>
